## Source of Truth (STRICT)

The ONLY source of truth for UI, layout, spacing, colors, typography, and component structure
is the code exported from Figma and located in the `/figma` directory.

No visual decisions may be made outside of this source.
If something is unclear or missing in Figma — do NOT guess, do NOT invent.
Use the closest existing pattern from the same Figma export.

## Figma Contract

The `/figma-design` directory contains generated UI code and assets.
This directory must be treated as a design contract.

Rules:

- Components must be derived from Figma code
- Class names, spacing, layout logic must follow Figma
- Refactoring is allowed ONLY for reusability, not visual changes
- Do NOT add new UI elements not present in Figma

## Forbidden Actions

- Do NOT redesign or "improve" UI
- Do NOT adjust spacing, colors, typography
- Do NOT add animations, transitions, or effects unless present in Figma
- Do NOT add new components or variants
- Do NOT change layout structure

## Design Rules

Layout structure must be reconstructed directly from Figma code.
No assumptions about UX or responsiveness are allowed.
If responsive behavior is not defined in Figma, keep desktop-only layout.

## Component Extraction Rules

Components may be extracted ONLY if they appear at least twice in Figma code.
Extraction must preserve original markup and styles.
No new props or variants unless required by Figma structure.

## Page Assembly Rules

Pages must be assembled strictly from existing components derived from Figma.
Pages must not introduce new layout or UI logic.